SIMPLE: tandem
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tandem
<hw>Tan"dem</hw> <pr>(t⟦acr⟧n"d⟦ecr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>adv. & a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>tandem</ets> at length (of time only), punningly taken as
meaning, lengthwise.]</ety> <def>One after another; -- said especially
of horses harnessed and driven one before another, instead of
abreast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tandem</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tandem
<hw>Tan"dem</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A team of horses
harnessed one before the other.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧He drove
<xex>tandems</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tandem bicycle or other vehicle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Tandem bicycle</b></col> <it>or</it> <col><b>Tandem
tricycle</b></col></mcol>, <cd>one for two persons in which one rider
sits before the other.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tandem cart</ent>⟦br⟧
